LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 144
BY REVENUE AND TAXATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO TAXATION; AMENDING CHAPTER 36, TITLE 63, IDAHO CODE, BY THE AD-
3 DITION OF A NEW SECTION 63-3622XX, IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE A SALES AND USE
4 TAX EXEMPTION FOR SMALL SELLERS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVID-
5 ING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Chapter 36, Title 63, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
8 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
9 ignated as Section 63-3622XX, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
10 63-3622XX. SMALL SELLER. (1) There is hereby exempted from the taxes
11 imposed by this chapter sales of tangible personal property made by an in-
12 dividual making small sales. A small seller shall not collect or remit any
13 state sales or use tax imposed by this chapter.
14 (2) For purposes of this section, "small seller" means an Idaho resi-
15 dent making sales that do not exceed five thousand dollars ($5,000) in cumu-
16 lative gross receipts in the current or previous calendar year. It shall not
17 include partnerships, corporations, or limited liability corporations.
18 (3) The exemption provided in this section shall not apply to:
19 (a) Sales of motor vehicles, trailers, all-terrain vehicles, utility
20 type vehicles, specialty off-highway vehicles, motorcycles intended
21 for off-road use, snowmobiles, aircraft, vessels as defined in section
22 67-7003, Idaho Code, alcohol, or tobacco; or
23 (b) Items purchased to be sold or incorporated into items to be sold.
24 (4) A small seller with gross receipts exceeding five thousand dollars
25 ($5,000) shall within thirty (30) days file with the state tax commission
26 an application for a temporary seller's permit and begin collecting sales
27 and use tax. No temporary seller's permit shall be issued for a period of
28 time greater than the remaining calendar year in which sales exceeded five
29 thousand dollars ($5,000) for a small seller. The following year, such
30 seller shall apply for a seller's permit under the provisions of section
31 63-3620(a), Idaho Code.
32 (5) A small seller shall indicate on such seller's invoice, if re-
33 quested by the purchaser, that the sale was exempt from sales and use tax
34 pursuant to the provisions of this section.
35 (6) A small seller shall not permanently maintain, occupy, or use an
36 office, place of distribution, sales or sample room or place, warehouse or
37 storage place, or other place of business or maintain a stock of goods with
38 anticipation of exceeding gross receipts of five thousand dollars ($5,000).
39 (7) A small seller may file an application with the state tax commission
40 for a seller's permit pursuant to section 63-3620, Idaho Code, before such
41 seller reaches the five thousand dollar ($5,000) threshold provided in sub-
42 section (2) of this section.

2
1 (8) Nothing in this section relieves a small seller from filing indi-
2 vidual income tax returns for persons who meet the filing requirements under
3 section 63-3030, Idaho Code.
4 (9) A small seller with sales exceeding three thousand dollars ($3,000)
5 annually shall keep such records for not less than four (4) years pursuant to
6 section 63-3624, Idaho Code.
7 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
8 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
9 July 1, 2025.

